# AWS Infrastructure Deployment via Local and Registry Terraform Modules

This project demonstrates how to mix **locally developed custom child modules** with **official community-maintained modules from the Terraform Registry** within a single root orchestration workspace.

---

## Project Directory Architecture

The repository is organized to separate root-level orchestrations from internal component files:

```text
.
├── main.tf                            # Root module: Instantiates official registry S3 and local EC2 modules
├── provide.tf                         # Root module: Configures the target AWS region
├── terra.tf                           # Root module: Defines provider versions and engine configurations
├── terraform.tfstate                  # Local active deployment state file
├── terraform.tfstate.backup           # Last known good state backup
└── own-terra-child-module-details    # Internal directory for custom module code
    └── ec2-own                        # Custom child module for isolated compute provisioning
        ├── data.tf                    # Dynamic Ubuntu AMI data source query
        └── main.tf                    # EC2 resource definitions and variable blocks

```

---

## Technical Task Roadmap & Implementations

### Task 1: Main Execution Core & Version Constraints (Root Module)

The root module handles provider version locking, region target configuration, and block orchestrations. Notably, the local S3 logic has been commented out and replaced with an verified registry module to implement vendor standard practices.

#### `terra.tf`

Specifies strict provider rules. The AWS provider constraint is set to `>= 6.42.0` to prevent dependency engine initialization locks.

```hcl
terraform {
  required_providers {
    aws = {
      source  = "hashicorp/aws"
      version = ">= 6.42.0"  # Set to handle upstream module dependency prerequisites
    }
    random = {
      source  = "hashicorp/random"
      version = "3.8.1"
    }
  }
}

```

#### `provide.tf`

Establishes default connection arguments for the primary infrastructure plane.

```hcl
# Configure the default AWS Provider to target the Mumbai region
provider "aws" {
  region = "ap-south-1"
}

```

#### `main.tf`

Implements the call blocks. The local storage module is decoupled in preference of an official public registry module.

```hcl
# Deprecated local module invocation - retained for architectural history tracking
#module "eco-s3" {
#  source = "./own-terra-child-module-details/s3-own"
#}

# Task 1a: Consume verified external modules from the public registry
module "s3-bucket" {                                     #imported module from terraform registry
  source  = "terraform-aws-modules/s3-bucket/aws"
  version = "5.14.0"

  bucket = "my-s3-bucket-from-imported-module"
}

# Task 1b: Consume unmanaged custom modules via local pathing references
module "eco-ec2" {
  source = "./own-terra-child-module-details/ec2-own"
}

```

